<input type="hidden" name="course" value="problemset">
<input type="hidden" name="task" value="1727">
There are $n$ children, and each of them independently gets a random integer number of candies between $1$ and $k$.<br />
<br />
What is the expected maximum number of candies a child gets?<br />
<br />
<b id="input">Input</b><br />
<br />
The only input line contains two integers $n$ and $k$.<br />
<br />
<b id="output">Output</b><br />
<br />
Print the expected number rounded to six decimal places.<br />
<br />
<b id="constraints">Constraints</b><br />
<ul>
<li>$1 \le n \le 100$<br />
<li>$1 \le k \le 100$<br />
</ul>
<b id="example">Example</b><br />
<br />
Input:<br />
<code>2 3</code><br />
<br />
Output:<br />
<code>2.444444</code>    </div>
